{"word":"παιδικός","slug":"παιδικός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παιδικός</b></el> <el>(παιδικός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:παῖς'><el>παῖς</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>of, for</i> or <i>like a child, boyish</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>puerilis</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>playful, sportive</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; so, <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-κῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>of</i> or <i>for a beloved youth</i>, <el>π. λόγος</el> a <i>love-</i> tale, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, <el>παιδικά, ῶν, τά</el>, <i>a darling, favourite</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>deliciae</el>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}